                        <provenance type="found" when="1852">One of two ogham stones (see also I-KIK-010) at this early church site, which also has a round tower (KK024-062004-). Discovered in 1852 standing close to the S wall of the church and <q>nine paces</q> from the round tower (Prim 1854, 87). 
                        </provenance>
                        <provenance type="observed">On site at Tullaherin, immediately S of the S wall of the nave of the medieval church (KK024-062001-), towards the W end.</provenance>
                    </history>
